KATSINA – Dr Ibrahim Mudi Kurfi, the Rector, of Hassan Usman Katsina Polytechnic has expressed the readiness of the institution to continue to uphold high-level discipline among its lecturers and students. Kurfi made this assertion while speaking with some journalists in his office. According to him, the institution under his leadership has zero tolerance for indiscipline and also frowned at the immoral excesses of graduating students of the institution. He added that it is immoral for a female student to sign on the bare shirt of her male counterpart, while it is equally immoral for a male to do likewise on the shirt of his female counterpart. “We here as an institution that promotes morality among students must join hands with parents and the society to check this immoral excess,” he advised. The Rector similarly stressed that the rate of examination malpractices and cultism are minimal in the institution.He, therefore, vowed that the institution will continue to uphold a high level of discipline among its lecturers and students and check all excesses amongst all. Kurfi however revealed that of the 32 courses run by the institution 28 were fully accredited, hoping to introduce more courses and secure accreditation for the unaccredited ones.